    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Engine Systems - Engine Systems - Engine Systems Interaction Diagram</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010101.6" svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Engine Systems Interaction Diagram</title>
        <figure id="f3050110" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj31/j31022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Engine systems interactions</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The primary engine systems are air management and fuel management which share some subsystems or have a
            subsystem that contributes to their operation.
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>The electronic control system controls the air management system and fuel management system.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The Coolant System provides heat transfer for crankcase and cylinder sleeves, cylinder head, EGR
                    gases, and lubrication oil.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The lube oil system provides lubrication and heat transfer for engine components.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The Injection Control Pressure (ICP) system uses engine oil to actuate the fuel injectors.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The fuel supply system pressurizes fuel to the fuel injectors.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcproc>
